Machakos governor aspirant Wavinya Ndeti has said she will not fold her political party Chama Cha Uzalendo and neither will she bow to the pressure of becoming anyone&rsquo;s running mate in the elections.Speaking on Sunday during her voter sensitisation campaign in Matuu, the former Kathiani MP said her name will be on the ballot. She told off politicians who have been urging her to fold her party and join Wiper.&ldquo;It must be known that Machakos belongs to all of us and residents have the right to elect a leader of their choice regardless of which party they contest on,&rdquo; she said.Ndeti urged the people of Machakos to rally behind her and vote for her as the next governor. &ldquo;I pledge to work with all of you, and give priority to your needs and not my own needs as a person, to bring the much-needed change in Machakos,&rdquo; she said.The CCU leader has been fighting off calls by several Wiper operatives led by Machakos Senator Johnson Muthama, to join Wiper and seek the party&rsquo;s ticket to contest the governor seat.